Tic Tac Toe Game
#Overview
Tic Tac Toe is a classic two-player game where players take turns marking spaces in a 3x3 grid. The player who succeeds in placing three of their marks in a horizontal, vertical, or diagonal row wins the game.

#How to Play
Setup: The game board consists of a 3x3 grid. Each player is assigned a symbol, usually 'X' and 'O'.

Taking Turns: Players take turns placing their symbol in an empty space on the grid.

Winning: The game is won by the player who successfully aligns three of their symbols either horizontally, vertically, or diagonally.

Draw: If all spaces on the grid are filled and no player has aligned three symbols, the game is a draw.

#Getting Started
To play the Tic Tac Toe game:

Open the game board.
Players take turns clicking on the empty spaces to place their symbol.
The game continues until one player wins or the game is a draw.
Players can restart the game at any time using the reset button.

